FBIS4-23377 "drafr108_a_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-108 Daily Report 3 Jun 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda RPF Says Egypt Continues To Arm Government Forces RPF Says Egypt Continues To Arm Government Forces EA0306190194 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura in French to Rwanda 1030 GMT 3 Jun 94 EA0306190194 (Clandestine) Radio Muhabura French BFN [Excerpts] It is worth noting that at a time when the international community is trying to assist Rwanda, it is to be regretted that the Egyptian Government continues to support the Rwandan Government clique which plunged the whole country into bloodshed. The Egyptian Government recently allowed Rwandan leaders to purchase 33 tonnes of arms, worth $765,000, as specified in a fax dated 25 May 1994 from Cairo, from the second secretary of the Rwandan Embassy to Egypt, Mr. (Jean-Baptiste Vikamira Baviri), to Defense Minister Augustin Bizimungu. [passage omitted] Most of the weapons used by the Rwandan Government are from Egypt, France, and South Africa, the apartheid South Africa. It is worth noting that today, democratic and nonsegregationist South Africa has made a positive change, as expected. Instead of backing a regime of butchers in Kibungo, Kibuye, or else in Gitarama, for it is no longer in Gitarama that the government is headquartered, South Africa agrees to provide humanitarian assistance [sentence as heard]. [passage omitted]
